The Internationalization Working Group has published a Working Draft of Requirements for Hangul Text Layout and Typography. This document describes requirements for general Korean language/Hangul text layout and typography realized with technologies like CSS, SVG and XSL-FO. The document is mainly based on a project to develop the international standard for Korean text layout. Learn [&#8230;]<img src="https://www.w3.org/analytics/piwik/piwik.php?idsite=7&amp;rec=1&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2Fblog%2Fnews%2Farchives%2F4789%3Fpk_campaign%3Dfeed%26pk_kwd%3Drequirements-for-hangul-text-layout-and-typography-draft-published-2&amp;action_name=Requirements+for+Hangul+Text+Layout+and+Typography+Draft+Published&amp;urlref=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2Fblog%2Fnews%2Ffeed" style="border:0;width:0;height:0" width="0" height="0" alt="" />
