<description>
<![CDATA[
The Web Applications Working Group has published a Working Draft of Service Workers. This specification describes a method that enables applications to take advantage of persistent background processing, including hooks to enable bootstrapping of web applications while offline. The core of this system is an event-driven Web Worker, which responds to events dispatched from documents [&#8230;]<img src="https://www.w3.org/analytics/piwik/piwik.php?idsite=7&amp;rec=1&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2Fblog%2Fnews%2Farchives%2F4777%3Fpk_campaign%3Dfeed%26pk_kwd%3Dservice-workers-draft-published-3&amp;action_name=Service+Workers+Draft+Published&amp;urlref=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2Fblog%2Fnews%2Ffeed" style="border:0;width:0;height:0" width="0" height="0" alt="" />
]]>
</description>
<content:encoded>
<![CDATA[
<p>The <a href="http://www.w3.org/2008/webapps/">Web Applications Working Group</a> has published a Working Draft of <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/2015/WD-service-workers-20150625/">Service Workers</a>. This specification describes a method that enables applications to take advantage of persistent background processing, including hooks to enable bootstrapping of web applications while offline. The core of this system is an event-driven Web Worker, which responds to events dispatched from documents and other sources. A system for managing installation, versions, and upgrades is provided. The service worker is a generic entry point for event-driven background processing in the Web Platform that is extensible by other specifications. Learn more about the <a href="http://www.w3.org/2006/rwc/">Rich Web Client Activity</a>.</p> <p><img src="https://www.w3.org/analytics/piwik/piwik.php?idsite=7&amp;rec=1&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2Fblog%2Fnews%2Farchives%2F4777%3Fpk_campaign%3Dfeed%26pk_kwd%3Dservice-workers-draft-published-3&amp;action_name=Service+Workers+Draft+Published&amp;urlref=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2Fblog%2Fnews%2Ffeed" style="border:0;width:0;height:0" width="0" height="0" alt="" /></p>
